The All Progressives Congress (APC) National Women Leader, Dr. Betta Edu, has flagged off a free healthcare programme that includes free surgeries to over 3000 residents of Zamfara. This is part of the activities marking the empowerment programme initiated by Betta for grassroots development in Zamfara State. She said it was imperative to support Governor Bello Matawalle’s efforts.   ‘Ekiti, Osun polls litmus test for 2023…     826 Plateau pilgrims set for Saudi Arabia     MSSN holds Ummahaat conference   She said one of the core factors that engenders personal and public development is quality of life provided by healthcare system. “Quality health is priority; the governor has done very well, and we will support him to reach out to more citizens, as well as internally displaced persons,” she said. Governor Matawalle said the development of Zamfara is incomplete without the basic development of the people. He said the people must be empowered along basic means of life as the government is building enabling environment for individuals to thrive. Wife of Zamfara State Governor, Hajia Aisha Matawalle urged the people to vote for the APC in the coming elections.